$ Oracle SQL: rename

The Oracle SQL verb `rename` allows to rename
  • → development/databases/Oracle/objects/tables[tables]
  • → development/databases/Oracle/objects/views[views]
  • → development/databases/Oracle/objects/sequences[sequences]
  • private synonyms

code {
rename oldName to newName;
code }

→ development/databases/Oracle/objects[Objects] that use the name of the renamed object become invalid after the object name was renamed.

{ Statistics

  Statistics are kept after renaming a table, as is demonstrated with the following example:
  gh|Oracle-Patterns|/SQL/rename/statistics.sql||

}


sa:
  → development/databases/Oracle/SQL/statement/nouns/table#ora-sql-alter-table-rename-column[`alter table … rename column …`].
